description: Ileana Garcia (Republican Party) is a member of the Florida State Senate, representing District 37. She assumed office on November 3, 2020. Her current term ends on November 8, 2022.

name: Manny Diaz, Jr.
title: State Senator (District 36)
description: Manny Diaz Jr. is a Republican member of the Florida State Senate, representing District 36. He was first elected to the chamber in 2018.

name: Shevrin D. Jones
title: State Senator (District 35)
description: Shevrin Jones (Democratic Party) (also known as Shev) is a member of the Florida State Senate, representing District 35. He assumed office on November 3, 2020. His current term ends on November 8, 2022.

name: Katherine Fernandez Rundle
title: State Attorney (Miami-Dade)
description: Katherine Fernandez Rundle (born March 1, 1950) is the current State Attorney for Miami-Dade County in Florida.

name: Nicole Fried
title: Commissioner of Agriculture
description: Nikki Fried (Democratic Party) is the Florida Commissioner of Agriculture and Consumer Services. She assumed office on January 8, 2019. Her current term ends on January 3, 2023.

name: Richard Corcoran
title: Commissioner of Education
description: Richard Corcoran was the Florida Commissioner of Education. Corcoran assumed office in 2018. Corcoran left office on April 30, 2022.

name: Jimmy Patronis
title: Chief Financial Officer
description: Jimmy Patronis (Republican Party) is the Florida Chief Financial Officer. He assumed office in 2017. His current term ends on January 3, 2023.

name: Ashley Moody
title: Attorney General
description: Ashley B. Moody (Republican Party) is the Attorney General of Florida. She assumed office on January 8, 2019. Her current term ends on January 3, 2023.

name: Cord Byrd
title: Acting Secretary of State
description: Cord Byrd is the acting Florida Secretary of State. Byrd was appointed by Gov. Ron DeSantis (R) to replace Laurel Lee (R), who resigned in May 2022. Byrd's confirmation is pending Senate confirmation.

name: Jeanette M. Nuñez
title: Lt. Governor
description: Jeanette Nuñez (Republican Party) is the Lieutenant Governor of Florida. She assumed office on January 8, 2019. Her current term ends on January 3, 2023.
